header.gameNote: FRESNO STATE TOURNAMENT AT FRESNO CA

article.headline: UC-Irvine 53, Winston-Salem 41
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Patrick Sanders scored 13 points as UC Irvine held Winston-Salem State to 28 percent shooting en route to a 53-41 victory Saturday night. Darrell Wonge had 17 points and eight rebounds for Winton-Salem State (0-2), which is playing its first season in Division I. Darren Fells and Michael Hunter added eight points each for UC Irvine (1-1). Fells also had eight rebounds. The Anteaters led 28-23 at halftime and played suffocating defense early in the second half, holding the Rams to 5-of-24 in shooting. Winston-Salem State did not score for more than 10 minutes as UC Irvine stretched its lead to 13 points. The Anteaters won handily despite committing 21 turnovers.
